<DOC><DOCNO> AP880405-0034 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-04-05-88 0337EDT</FILEID><FIRST>r i PM-BRF--Britain-Fire     04-05 0127</FIRST><SECOND>PM-BRF--Britain-Fire,0131</SECOND><HEAD>Three Children Die In House Fire</HEAD><DATELINE>BIRMINGHAM, England (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   A woman who left her burning home tocall the fire department returned to find the blaze had killed herthree children.   Laura McClaren, 32, who rushed to a neighbor's to call for help,found that the front door of her home had slammed and locked whenshe left.   When fire officials arrived and broke down the door Mondaynight, they found Dominique McClaren, 3, and her brother Alec, 7,unconscious in a bathroom. Both died soon after they were carriedout of the house.   Their 6-year-old brother Simon was found dead in another room ofthe row house in the city's Edgbaston district.   Mrs. McClaren was hospitalized with head, back and hand injuries.</TEXT></DOC>